If you are looking for a large scale urban combat arena, then this is one of the better maps to do it on. The city's scale is immense, with blocks and blocks of buildings, cars and assorted debris. Even with all of this open area, there is also a few fully model interiors to make for some short cuts through the city. Once of these areas goes through a water treatment facility and up to one of the bomb sites, which is in a small auto garage. The map quality is great, and gives you that sense that you are fighting in an urban setting. The buildings, sidewalks, utilities and so forth are modeled with great detail. This map supports up to 64 players, and with that many players, not a single tile will go untrampled in the largest of battles.

_sText: For this map i tried to make a copy of the zombie panic source map zpo_cinema, and i think i have made a good job. This map is in a city enviroment and has a setup looking like the de_dust2. Terrorist starts outside, and has the mission to blow up one of three saloons. A and B bombsite are both saloons. There are fast ways to get to the bombsites, but those will shure be guarded by ct's. So i made he map in three floors: basement, first floor, secong floor. The basement is a great way to get behind ct lines and take em by surprise, but be carful as a t, you never know if there is a ct hiding in the darkness of the basement. the first floor is entré, saloons and links between them, this is the floor were both the bombsites are located. The second floor is not big, but you have a great overview. I also have a outside enviroment. There is not much taken place out there but, it's a nice and goodlooking area where you choose wich way you want to go, as a t. The ct's starts in the basement. There you can fast reach the bombsites. The map includes alot of stairs, because of the 3 floors, so be awake and watch for enemies around every corner. There are two openings to every bombsite, so there is hard to hold a bombsite at your own. Make shure you arenot running around like a freak and jumping around, the enemies will hear you, trust me. That was it and i hope you will enjoy my map! =)

I made this map for a friend in CSS named Chexer. He wanted me to make a texture map for him, and although I suck at making them, I accepted his request and went for it trying the best I could to make this for him.

This map was originally de_bombextreme, one of my very first maps made. I took my old design and fixed it up, making new things such as better spawn points, teleporters, buy zones, a sky box, water and I added lights. 

The maps starts off with the Terrorists underground in tunnels and they have several different ways they can go to get to the surface where CTs wait their arrival. You can either go up 1 of the 2 huge flights of stairs and get into the main area through the top of the map or you can go through one of the six teleporters which will teleport you to a block somewhere in the CT spawn. You have to shoot out one of the sides to get out of the block, but it's really a very stealthy way to get into the CT's spawn area and the bomb site. Or if you wanted to you could just simply run up the main ramp and go straight for a kamikazi rush into the CT spawn.

As a CT you start out in the main area of the map where all the action happens. The first few seconds are calm and quiet. But when the Ts get into one of the many areas to get into the map, the CTs must be prepared to guard the bomb site from the many areas that the Ts will come from.

DE CHANGES 2 by MasterW3
The terrorists will be assaulting two of four known targets.  
Only TWO of these targets will be active, marked by signs on the billboards, according to our sources.
You will also be told which sites are active, as well as a Weather Update, by the Console.

The potential targets are as follows:   
A: the TRUCK that the barrels are shipped to the warehouse in. They may plant an explosive inside the vehicle.  
B: the Warehouse that loads the barrels onto the train could be a target.  that would shut down the whole operation.  
C: a Waste Storage Tower near the warehouse may also be a target.  By creating a massive spill, they could be making a statement about the dangers of these chemicals they believe to be toxic.  
D: We also believe that there may be evidence of alien life on a truck at a nearby Terminal Hotel.  The government may be using this group to destroy this potential evidence.  Stop them at all costs, the world has a right to know if this is true.

de_cfactor

Map by MarkQ/Turd Furguson

Cremecorp is a company that supplies local twinkie factories with fresh creme filling. But as some have discovered, Cremecorp has a secret. It recovers the ubitquious filling with material from raw sewage. 
From an ingenious system devised by an expert architect, a four-step process takes the softest parts of the sewage and ferments it into fresh creme filling. Disgusted Terrorists has decided to stop this process, either midway in the processing step, or in the final step of export. Due to an anonymous tip, Cremecorp has mobilized it's

I've been working on this for a while, but it's my first release.
